{"id": 231287370, "title": "Man pushed down stairs in 'cowardly attack' and has life-changing injuries", "text": "A man, 52, sustained \"life-changing\" injuries after being shoved down a flight of stairs in Altrincham. Greater Manchester Police (GMP) is now searching for leads, and appealed for information. At about 2.10am on Saturday (June 8), GMP was informed of an incident that occurred on the Causeway. A man had been sent tumbling down a staircase, landing him in hospital where he's still battling his injuries. Police are yet to make any arrests, but the investigation is already moving at pace. They're urging anyone with information to come forward, as soon as possible. Investigation chief Detective Inspector Andrew Langlands of Salford CID said: \"This was a cowardly attack which left a man with serious injuries. Our investigation is moving at pace, and we are undertaking exhaustive enquiries to identify and arrest the person - or persons responsible.\" He continued: \"We are now appealing to anyone who may have witnessed this incident, or who has information to share (including relevant CCTV, mobile or dashcam footage) to make a report to police as soon as possible.\", reports the Manchester Evening News. If you have any information, you can phone the police on 0161 856 9164 quoting log 290 of 08/06/2024.", "summary": "A man was pushed down some stairs in Altrincham during the early hours of Saturday morning, and Greater Manchester Police is now appealing for anyone with information to come forward", "url": "https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/breaking-man-pushed-down-stairs-32989144", "image": "https://i2-prod.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/article32989142.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_the-causeway.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 14:49:50", "author": "Joseph Timan", "authors": ["Joseph Timan"], "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.451}